c=http://www.geocities.com/Pipeline/7721/sm_daggers.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Kuurus has slain his last foe</span><hr size=1> I have been thinking about this for some time now.  The non-implementaion of any real rogue skills and our inability to bring anything worthwhile to a group were the foundation of my disenchantment with the game.  Then upon the foundation of the Sanguine Blade (all rogue guild on Bristlebane) I had a reason to play again, and was also holding out hope for meaningful change. <BR>  <BR> 2 things happened to dim my view.  The petition was summarily dismissed without so much as a &quot;Thanks for your input&quot; and I read Akak's retirement notice.  I found that I am in much the same situation as he when I stopped to think about it.  For something that I am not entirely happy with, I spend WAY too much time on this game, neglecting other things I need to do.  I have finally found the strength to say enough is enough.  Kuurus has been retired, my account has been cancelled. <BR>  <BR> Thank you all for the Safehouse.  Your input and advice has been a tremendous help.  I would never have gotten as much out of the game had I not been introduced to this wonderful place so long ago.  All that is left now is for me to follow Modus' lead and let Verant know how thier neglecting of our class has played such a huge role in me reaching this decision.  Hopefully, adding my voice in that respect will help.  Perhaps if they would not listen to a reasonable petition, they will start to listen when they see cancellations affecting their bottom line instead.  I have seen that Smed has started a dialogue here and sincerely hope that those of you remaining get what you deserve in attention to the class.  It has just taken too long to be of any value to me.  Farewell. <BR>  <p>Kuurus IceBear<BR>
Sanguine Blade, Bristlebane <BR>
<BR>
Marlenus<BR>
Shank and killer of all things non-barbarian on Vallon
<BR>
<BR>
"I have no quarrel with you sir - (at least not until you turn your back that is)."

